3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper uses graph-based representations of user data, which is a common technique in social and information networks research. 
4. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed approach, which involves software engineering aspects such as data representation and feature extraction. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses graph-based data structures and algorithms for feature extraction and recommendation tasks.
